00:02:27,297 --> 00:02:29,839
is creating, game balance is creating

44
00:02:29,919 --> 00:02:31,521
the appearance of fairness in a game.

45
00:02:31,941 --> 00:02:33,343
And appearance is really important here.

46
00:02:33,444 --> 00:02:35,627
It's about player perception as much as reality,

47
00:02:36,027 --> 00:02:38,691
because as game designers, we are crafting an experience.

48
00:02:38,831 --> 00:02:40,334
And it's that experience that matters.

49
00:02:40,954 --> 00:02:44,299
So balance is part math, part systems, and part psychology.

50
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,022
We do this through several methods.

51
00:02:46,703 --> 00:02:51,066
One is designer intuition or experience. The game designer chooses to make certain things

52
00:02:51,106 --> 00:02:55,208
a certain way because it feels right to them. Another is play testing. You create a rapid

53
00:02:55,228 --> 00:02:59,631
prototype, play on your own or with friends, observe and make changes based on any rules,

54
00:02:59,691 --> 00:03:03,253
exploits or weaknesses that you find. Play testing is another thing that everyone has

